The clojure-cassandra project is a wrapper around the existing Java Thrift client for the Cassandra database.

Usage:

(require ['cassandra :as 'db])

(def client (db/make-client "host" port))

(db/insert client "table" "key" "column-parent" {:col-a (.getBytes "alice" "UTF-8") 
                                              :col-b (.getBytes "bob" "UTF-8"})

(into {} (map (fn [[k v]] [k (String. v)]) 
              (db/get client "table" "key" "column-parent" [:col-a :col-b])))

;; Returns: {:col-a "alice" :col-b "bob"} 
